  01 Feb 2015; Michael Palimaka <kensington@gentoo.org> -k9copy-2.3.8.ebuild:
  Remove old.

  01 Feb 2015; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> k9copy-2.3.8-r1.ebuild:
  Stable for x86, wrt bug #538082

  31 Jan 2015; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> k9copy-2.3.8-r1.ebuild:
  Stable for amd64, wrt bug #538082

  10 Aug 2014; Patrick Lauer <patrick@gentoo.org> k9copy-2.3.8-r1.ebuild,
  k9copy-2.3.8.ebuild:
  Fix description for more repoman happy

  04 Apr 2014; Johannes Huber <johu@gentoo.org>
  +files/k9copy-2.3.8-ffmpeg-2.1.patch, k9copy-2.3.8-r1.ebuild:
  Add patch to fix build with ffmpeg-2.2 by eroen <eroen@faith.eroen.eu>, bug
  #505196.

*k9copy-2.3.8-r1 (19 Mar 2014)

  19 Mar 2014; Johannes Huber <johu@gentoo.org> +k9copy-2.3.8-r1.ebuild:
  Revision bump to EAPI 5.

  26 Feb 2014; Michael Palimaka <kensington@gentoo.org> k9copy-2.3.8.ebuild:
  Depend on media-video/ffmpeg instead of virtual/ffmpeg wrt bug #474394.

  03 Mar 2013; Alexis Ballier <aballier@gentoo.org> k9copy-2.3.8.ebuild,
  +files/k9copy-2.3.8-ffmpeg-0.11.patch,
  +files/k9copy-2.3.8-includepaths.patch:
  Import slackware patch to build with recent ffmpeg versions and port the
  patch from backlite to properly include ffmpeg headers, bug #459980

  12 Jul 2012; Michael Palimaka <kensington@gentoo.org> metadata.xml:
  Cleanup metadata.

  23 Apr 2012; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> k9copy-2.3.8.ebuild:
  Stable for amd64, wrt bug #412803

  08 Mar 2012; Sebastian Pipping <sping@gentoo.org> k9copy-2.3.8.ebuild:
  Guard optional mplayer runtime dependency behind mplayer use flag so that
  people who (1) have mplayer2 installed (which conflicts with mplayer) and (2)
  use the internal preview of k9copy can still install k9copy without problems

